text: Coins are a lot more useful than people think. The most obvious benefit is the increase to your max speed, but they also have other uses. First, If you have a coin in your first item slot, you are guarantee to get a defensive item, like a banana or a shell, next item box. Second, it gives a defense against Boos. If you hold to a coin instead of using it right away to get to your defensive item, the boo will steall the coin, leaving you with a defensive item and the theif with something that give them a miminal (if they have >10 coins) to no (if they have 10 coins) advantage

text:
One of the biggest tips I can offer in this game is to hold the item button when you get a throwable item like a shell, banana, or bomb. This makes your character hold the item on the back of your cart, which does three things. First, it frees up an item slot, letting you hold a maximum of three items. Second, if you have a banana or shell it will actually block incoming items(cough cough red shells) that would otherwise hit you, essentially using an item to counter another item and maintain your momentum. Third, letting go of the button while holding in the direction you want to throw it will allow you to throw the item as if you had just pushed the button, meaning that there is literally no downside to using this trick. I figured this out just randomly and it's just a minute little thing to help improve.

Also side note, use coins when you get them in an item slot as soon as you can. They do nothing but take up an item slot and there's no reason why you shouldn't just immediately use it.

Edit: Sorry, I made this comment before actually watching the vod and gura is so pro she already knows to do this so good on her. Also I was wrong about saving an item slot, that was only true in the DS version apparently. My bad, have a nice day
